        <body>
            <div>

	<gb type="book-pages"/>

<!-- The pages of this part of the diary, as laid out on the leaves, are not in numerical order and were transcribed out of order initially. However, I have rearranged them into the proper order in which they should now be kept. AW -->

	<pb facs="liv_000206_0001" n="LXII"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297e_069-062_001r_0_C_color" n="0062"/>--><!-- We should do a final review of all file names throughout the 1870 diary to make sure they are correct. AW -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><fw n="heading_LXII">LXII</fw> <date when="1870-11-22">22<hi rend="sup underline">nd</hi> <choice><abbr>Nov<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi></abbr><expan>November</expan></choice> 1870</date> copied foregoing despatch - It
<lb/>will be delivered by <persName ref="people.xml#pers0002"><choice><orig>Muhammad</orig><reg>Muhamad</reg></choice> Bogharib</persName> into the <term type="occupation">consul</term>'s
<lb/>hands at <placeName><geogName type="island" ref="geogName.xml#geog0060">Zanzibar</geogName></placeName></p><!-- Interesting reference. Mohamad Bogharbi is also, I believe, the fellow who carried the letter from Bambarre. AW -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><date when="1870-11-24">24<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> <choice><abbr>Nov<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi></abbr><expan>November</expan></choice></date> <term type="ailment" ref="ailment.xml#ailm0012">Herpes</term> is common at the plantations <!-- Has DL switched inks starting with this line? AW -->
<lb/>in <placeName><geogName type="island" ref="geogName.xml#geog0060">Zanzibar</geogName></placeName> but the close crowding of the houses
<lb/>in the town <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>they think prevents it. The lips &amp;
<lb/>mouth are affected &amp; constipation sets in for 3
<lb/>days - <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>cured by going over to mainland
<lb/>Affections<!-- Does he mean infections? AW --> of the lungs are cured by residence at
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="town"><choice><sic>Bariva</sic><corr>Barawa</corr></choice></settlement></placeName> or <placeName><settlement type="town">Brava</settlement></placeName> and also on mainland</p>
<lb/><p><choice><sic>the</sic><corr>The</corr></choice> Safari of <persName ref="people.xml#pers0043">Halzani</persName> took <bibl>my letters</bibl> from
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="village" ref="settlement.xml#sett0014">Ujiji</settlement></placeName> but person employed I do not know</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><date when="1870-11-25">25<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> <choice><abbr>Nov</abbr><expan>November</expan></choice></date> <choice><sic>wrote</sic><corr>Wrote</corr></choice> to <persName ref="people.xml#pers0080">Tom</persName> <persName ref="people.xml#pers0076">Agnes</persName> - <persName ref="people.xml#pers0194">Young</persName> - <persName ref="people.xml#pers0192">Webb</persName> 
<lb/><persName ref="people.xml#pers0229">Oswell</persName> <add place="above"><persName ref="people.xml#pers0045">D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Hamilton</persName></add> <persName ref="people.xml#pers0132">Sir Roderick</persName> <space extent="2" unit="chars"/><persName ref="people.xml#pers0036">Sir Bartle Frere</persName> -
<lb/><persName ref="people.xml#pers0189">Tracey</persName> - <persName ref="people.xml#pers0176">Stearns</persName> of <placeName><settlement type="city">Bombay</settlement></placeName> - <persName ref="people.xml#pers0087">Maclear</persName> = <persName ref="people.xml#pers0021">Bleek</persName>
<lb/><persName ref="people.xml#pers0079">Brother John</persName> in <placeName><country>Canada</country></placeName> = <space extent="2" unit="chars"/><bibl>Letters</bibl> to be delivered<!-- Incredibly, a lot of these letters have survived. We need to check how many of them we already have. AW -->
<lb/>by <persName ref="people.xml#pers0002"><choice><orig>Muhammad</orig><reg>Muhamad</reg></choice> Bogharib</persName> into <persName ref="people.xml#pers0144"><choice><abbr>Col</abbr><expan>Colonel</expan></choice> Playfair</persName> or <persName ref="people.xml#pers0071">D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Kirk</persName>'s
<lb/>own hands at <placeName><geogName type="island" ref="geogName.xml#geog0060">Zanzibar</geogName></placeName> - <persName ref="people.xml#pers0070"><choice><abbr>L<hi rend="sup">t</hi></abbr><expan>Lieutenant</expan></choice> Kinnaird</persName> &amp; <persName ref="people.xml#pers0022"><choice><abbr>B</abbr><expan>Bevan</expan></choice> Braithwaite</persName></p><!-- Stains at the end of these lines. AW -->

	<pb facs="liv_000206_0002" n="LXIII"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297e_063-068_001v_0_B_color" n="0063"/>-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><fw n="heading_LXIII">LXIII</fw> <date when="1870-11-29">29<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> <choice><abbr>Nov<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi></abbr><expan>November</expan></choice> 1870</date> <foreign xml:lang="und"><term xml:lang="und" ref="foreign-word.xml#frgn0012"><term type="ailment" ref="ailment.xml#ailm0019"><hi rend="double-underline">Safura</hi></term></term></foreign> is the name of the
<lb/>disease clay or earth eating at <placeName><geogName type="island" ref="geogName.xml#geog0060">Zanzibar</geogName></placeName> = It <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>often <!-- Stain at edge here. AW -->
<lb/>affects <orgName>slaves</orgName> and the clay is said to have a pleasant
<lb/>odour to the eaters, but it is not confined to <orgName>slaves</orgName>
<lb/>nor do <orgName>slaves</orgName> <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>eat in order to kill themselves - It is
<lb/>a diseased appetite and sick men who have plenty 
<lb/>to eat are often subject to it - The feet swell
<lb/>flesh is lost - and the face looks haggard - The
<lb/>patient can scarcely walk for shortness of breath
<lb/>and weakness and he continues eating till he
<lb/>dies = Here many <orgName>slaves</orgName> are now diseased with
<lb/><foreign xml:lang="und"><term xml:lang="und" ref="foreign-word.xml#frgn0012"><term type="ailment" ref="ailment.xml#ailm0019"><choice><orig>safura</orig><reg>Safura</reg></choice></term></term></foreign> The clay built in walls is preferred and
<lb/><orgName><term type="tribe" ref="ethnic-group.xml#ethnic0010">Manyema</term> women</orgName> when pregnant often eat it.
<lb/>The cure is effected by drastic purges for seven
<lb/>days and nothing of <add place="below">^</add> <add place="above"><term type="animal">fish</term></add><!-- Fish is also food in this context, but I don't think we've consistently marked it that way. AW --> <term type="foodstuff">butter</term> - <term type="foodstuff">milk</term> or <term type="foodstuff">beef</term> must
<lb/>enter his mouth for <subst><del><unclear cert="medium">three</unclear></del><add place="over-text"><unclear cert="medium">two</unclear></add></subst><!--Looks like "two" but I think the letter "a" is also above -AK --><!-- See what I've done. AW --> years after it -- <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>old
<lb/><term type="foodstuff">vinegar</term> or <term type="plant">cocoa trees</term> put into a large <choice><sic>bason</sic><corr>basin</corr></choice> &amp;
<lb/>old slag made red hot cast into it - Then "<foreign xml:lang="und">Mbuye</foreign> <add place="below">^</add> <add place="above"><term type="plant_foodstuff">asofoetida</term></add>"
<lb/>1/2 a rupee in weight - . copperas <choice><abbr>sulph</abbr><expan cert="medium">sulphate</expan></choice> <choice><abbr>D<hi rend="sup">o</hi></abbr><expan>Ditto</expan></choice> <!-- Think sulph may be abbr for sulphate? HB --><!-- Coded. AW -->
<lb/>a small glass of this fasting morning &amp; evening<!-- Continues onto next page, so no </p> here. AW -->

	<pb facs="liv_000206_0003" n="LXIV"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297e_067-064_002r_0_B_color" n="0064"/>-->
<lb/><fw n="heading_LXIV"><hi rend="underline">LXIV</hi></fw> produces vomiting &amp; purging of black dejections - <!-- Again, this sentence continues from previous page. We probably don't need the <p> although including it is our usual practice. AW -->
<lb/>This is continued for seven days - no <term type="foodstuff">meat</term> eaten but
<lb/>only old <term type="plant_foodstuff">rice</term> or <term type="plant_foodstuff">dura</term> &amp; water - a <term type="animal">fowl</term><!-- Animal also food in this context. AW --> in course of time
<lb/>no <add place="below">^</add> <add place="above"><term type="animal">fish</term></add> <term type="foodstuff">butter</term> <term type="foodstuff">eggs</term> or <term type="foodstuff">beef</term> for two years on pain of death
<lb/><persName ref="people.xml#pers0002">Muhamad</persName>'s father had skill in the cure and the
<lb/>above is his prescription - <foreign xml:lang="und"><term xml:lang="und" ref="foreign-word.xml#frgn0012"><term type="ailment" ref="ailment.xml#ailm0019">Safura</term></term></foreign> is thus a 
<lb/>disease per se - It is common in <term type="tribe" ref="ethnic-group.xml#ethnic0010">Manyema</term> &amp; 
<lb/>makes me in a measure content to wait for
<lb/>my medicines - from the description <w>inspiss-
<lb break="no"/>ated</w> bile seems to be the agent of blocking up the
<lb/>gall duct and duodenum and the clay <subst><del><gap extent="1" unit="words"/></del><add place="over-text">or</add></subst> earth
<lb/>may be nature trying to clean it away - <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>the
<lb/>clay appears unchanged in the stools and in
<lb/>large quantity a <orgName><term type="tribe" ref="ethnic-group.xml#ethnic0014"><choice><orig>Banyamwezi</orig><reg>Nyamwezi</reg></choice></term>  <term type="occupation">carrier</term></orgName> who
<lb/>bore an enormous load of copper is now by <foreign xml:lang="und"><term xml:lang="und" ref="foreign-word.xml#frgn0012"><term type="ailment" ref="ailment.xml#ailm0019">Safura</term></term></foreign>
<lb/>scarcely able to walk - He took it at <placeName><geogName type="river" ref="geogName.xml#geog0033">Lualaba</geogName></placeName> where
<lb/>food is abundant &amp; he is contented with his lot -<!-- Stain to review. AW -->
<lb/><space extent="1" unit="words"/>squeeze a fingernail &amp; if no blood appears beneath it
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="words"/><foreign xml:lang="und"><term xml:lang="und" ref="foreign-word.xml#frgn0012"><term type="ailment" ref="ailment.xml#ailm0019">Safura</term></term></foreign> is the cause <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>of the bloodlessness -<!-- Continues onto next page, so no </p> here. AW -->

	<pb facs="liv_000206_0004" n="LXV"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297e_065-066_002v_0_B_color" n="0065"/>-->
<lb/><fw n="heading_LXV">LXV</fw> a dread of encountering this disease without any
<lb/>any medicine reconciles me partially to this detention</p> <!-- Stain at end of line. AW -->
<lb/><milestone unit="section" rend="line"/>
<lb/><p><date when="1870-12-02">2 <choice><abbr>Dec<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi></abbr><expan>December</expan></choice> 1870</date> <foreign xml:lang="und"><term xml:lang="und" ref="foreign-word.xml#frgn0014"><term type="animal">Sokos</term></term></foreign> collect together and make a drumming 
<lb/>noise some say with hollow trees then burst forth
<lb/>into loud yells well imitated by the <orgName>natives</orgName> - If a man
<lb/>has no spear <foreign xml:lang="und"><term xml:lang="und" ref="foreign-word.xml#frgn0014"><term type="animal">Sokos</term></term></foreign> goes away satisfied - If
<lb/>wounded he <choice><sic>siezes</sic><corr>seizes</corr></choice> the wrist lops off ends of the 
<lb/>fingers and spits them out - slaps the cheeks
<lb/>of his victim and bites without breaking the
<lb/>skin - draws out a spear but never uses
<lb/>it - takes some leaves and stuffs them into
<lb/>his wound to stanch the blood = Does not
<lb/>wish an encounter with an armed man = He 
<lb/>sees women do him no harm &amp; never molests them
<lb/>a man without a spear is nearly safe from him
<lb/>They beat hollow trees as drums with hands
<lb/>and then scream as music to it. When men
<lb/>hear them they go to <foreign xml:lang="und"><term xml:lang="und" ref="foreign-word.xml#frgn0014"><term type="animal">Sokos</term></term></foreign> but <foreign xml:lang="und"><term xml:lang="und" ref="foreign-word.xml#frgn0014"><term type="animal">Sokos</term></term></foreign> never
<lb/>goes to men <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>with hostility - <term type="tribe" ref="ethnic-group.xml#ethnic0010">Manyema</term> say "<foreign xml:lang="und"><term xml:lang="und" ref="foreign-word.xml#frgn0014"><term type="animal">Sokos</term></term></foreign>
<lb/>is a man" "&amp; nothing bad in him" a <foreign xml:lang="und"><term xml:lang="und" ref="foreign-word.xml#frgn0014"><term type="animal">Soko</term></term></foreign> was killed
<lb/>near this with holes in his ears - He had died a man &amp; <choice><sic>risen</sic><corr>rose</corr></choice> a <foreign xml:lang="und"><term xml:lang="und" ref="foreign-word.xml#frgn0014"><term type="animal">Soko</term></term></foreign></p>

	<pb facs="liv_000206_0004" n="LXVI"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297e_065-066_002v_0_B_color" n="0066"/>-->	
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><fw n="heading_LXVI">LXVI.</fw> <choice><sic>opinion</sic><corr>Opinion</corr></choice> and facts - 2 <term type="animal">Rhinoceroses</term> <unclear><app><rdg>scary</rdg><rdg>story</rdg></app></unclear>
<lb/>chivalry - <persName ref="people.xml#pers0048">Helmore</persName> found by <persName ref="people.xml#pers0017">Baldwin</persName> starving no
<lb/><term type="occupation">hunter</term> - no <term type="animal">horses</term> no <term type="occupation">medical man</term> - <persName ref="people.xml#pers0162">Sekeletu</persName>
<lb/>blamed though he got not £8000 to place him
<lb/>on Healthy <placeName><region ref="region.xml#region0016">Highlands</region></placeName> and I was accused as <!-- Is healthy highlands a euphemism for road to recovery, or should highlands be tagged as region here? HB --><!-- Region. AW -->
<lb/>morally guilty of his death though no letter was
<lb/>sent to me - saying <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>he had come <add place="below">^</add> <add place="above">or gone</add> to <placeName><region ref="region.xml#region0009">Linyanti</region></placeName></p>
<lb/><p><space extent="4" unit="chars"/><term type="occupation">Bishop</term> addressed no teaching - <term type="tribe" ref="ethnic-group.xml#ethnic0008"><choice><orig>Makololo</orig><reg>Kololo</reg></choice></term><!-- Stain. AW -->
<lb/>followed me and I was blamed because they 
<lb/>vitialed all <hi rend="underline">the teaching</hi> - then being none as
<lb/>2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> <term type="occupation">Bishop</term> said to me an astounding fact
<lb/>that people living with them have been taught
<lb/>absolutely nothing - Idleness was the bane of
<lb/>that mission and then loitering in the swamps
<lb/>killed them - I bore the accusations in 
<lb/>silence - I felt that so to do was chivalrous -
<lb/>Loss of heat or presence of mind - <persName ref="people.xml#pers0009">Absalom</persName>
<lb/><persName ref="people.xml#pers0157">Saul</persName> -</p><!-- It looks like this paragraph about the missionary deaths was cut from the Last Journals, which is sort of interesting. MW --><!-- Indeed worth noting. Also, DL's writing is quite disjointed here, maybe because he's ill? AW -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><date when="1870-12-06">6<hi rend="sup underline">th</hi> <choice><abbr>Dec<hi rend = "sup underline">r</hi></abbr><expan>December</expan></choice> 1870</date> <choice><sic>oh</sic><corr>Oh</corr></choice> for <persName ref="people.xml#pers0035">Dugumbe</persName> or <persName ref="people.xml#pers0181">Syde</persName>. !! to come
<lb/>but this delay may all be for the best.</p>

	<pb facs="liv_000206_0003" n="LXVII"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297e_067-064_002r_0_B_color" n="0067"/>-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><fw n="heading_LXVII">LXVII.</fw> The <term type="animal">Parrots</term> all seize their food &amp; hold it with the
<lb/>left hand - the <term type="animal">Lion</term> too is left handed - He strikes with
<lb/>his left - so are all animals - left handed save man.</p>
<lb/><milestone unit="section" rend="line"/>
<lb/><p>I noticed a very pretty woman come on marriage <space extent="2" unit="chars"/>with <persName ref="people.xml#pers0120"><w>Mona<supplied>-</supplied>
<lb break="no"/>mosimba</w></persName> past this quite jauntily about a month ago
<lb/>ten <term type="animal">goats</term> were given - Her friends came and asked
<lb/>another <term type="animal">goat</term> which being refused she was enticed away
<lb/>became sick of <term type="ailment" ref="ailment.xml#ailm0017">Rheumatic Fever</term> two days afterward
<lb/>and died yesterday - not a syllable of regret for the 
<lb/>beautiful young creature but for the <term type="animal">goats</term> "Oh"
<lb/>"our ten <term type="animal">goats</term>" <space extent="1" unit="words"/>they cannot grieve too much - "Our<choice><sic>"</sic><corr/></choice><!-- Stain to review. AW -->
<lb/>ten <term type="animal">goats</term>! Oh Oh"!</p>
<lb/><p><space extent="3" unit="chars"/><term type="tribe" ref="ethnic-group.xml#ethnic0015"><choice><orig><choice><sic>Basang</sic><corr>Basango</corr></choice></orig><reg>Sangu</reg></choice></term> wail over those who die in bed but not
<lb/>over those who die in battle = The <term type="animal">cattle</term> are a salve
<lb/>for all sores - women even raise no wailing</p>
<lb/><p><space extent="4" unit="chars"/>Another man killed in a village within <add place="below">^</add> <add place="above"><measure><choice><orig>½</orig><reg>1/2</reg></choice> miles</measure></add> sight<!--I think it says "12" above this next word that I also can't make out. -AK--><!-- I've corrected and transcribed as I see it. MW --><!-- More corection. AW -->
<lb/>of this - <space extent="3" unit="chars"/>They quarrelled and there is virtually no
<lb/><term type="occupation">chief</term> - the man was stabbed and village burned and
<lb/>people all fled - They are truly a bloody people -</p><!-- Interesting discoloration here worth processing. AW -->

	<pb facs="liv_000206_0002" n="LXVIII"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297e_063-068_001v_0_B_color" n="0068"/>-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><fw n="heading_LXVIII">LXVIII</fw> <foreign xml:lang="und"><term xml:lang="und" ref="foreign-word.xml#frgn0014"><term type="animal">Sokos</term></term></foreign> live in communities of about ten each having his 
<lb/>own female - an intruder from another camp is beaten off with 
<lb/>their fists and loud yells - If one tries to seize the female of another
<lb/>he is <gap extent="2" unit="chars" agent="blot"/> caught on the ground and all unite in boxing &amp;
<lb/>biting the offender - a male often carries a child
<lb/>especially if they are passing from one patch of forest
<lb/>to another over a grassy space - He then gives it to the
<lb/>mother</p>
<lb/><p><space extent="3" unit="chars"/><choice><sic>a</sic><corr>A</corr></choice> man died near this <persName ref="people.xml#pers0120">Monasimba</persName> went to
<lb/>his wife and after intercourse and washing he
<lb/>may appear among men - <space extent="1" unit="words"/>If no widow
<lb/>can be obtained he must sit naked behind
<lb/>his house till some one happens to die - all the
<lb/>lowest of the low - and especially in bloodiness
<lb/>the man who killed a woman without cause
<lb/>goes free - He offered his grandmother to be 
<lb/>killed in his stead and after a great deal of talk
<lb/>nothing was done to him - !</p>

	<pb facs="liv_000206_0001" n="LXIX"/>
	<!--<pb facs="DLC297e_069-062_001r_0_C_color" n="0069"/>-->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><fw n="heading_LXIX"><hi rend="underline">LXIX</hi></fw> <date when="1870-12-08">8 <choice><abbr>Dec<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi></abbr><expan>December</expan></choice> 1870</date> - <persName ref="people.xml#pers0178">Suleiman bin Juma</persName> lived on the
